The paper discusses the problem of knowledge discovery on web-scale data with diverse text sources, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed algorithm for aggregating multiple collections into a single hierarchical topic model involves techniques from deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a web service to demonstrate the concept of topical exploratory search suggests a focus on web-based applications (cs.DB).
